The paper discusses the privacy properties of Bayesian differential privacy, which is a topic related to cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also involves mathematical analysis and information theory (cs.IT), as well as machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with the partitioning of databases (cs.DB) and the composition of algorithms (cs.DS).
